replies.body:
Thanks for the response, Porocles. I figured that was the case, but I just wanted to be sure. It wouldn't have been a big deal if I hadn't been in my promotion series with one won already. Also, it would be unfortunate to have some sort of extended queue time for something completely out of my control. 

I read the Loss Prevented guide, and I think I understand. It is basically only activated when something happens on Riot's end that is not players' fault and they know it will negatively impact the games they are currently playing, right? It is never used for instances such as blackouts, power outages, internet outages, etc. that are not directly associated with Riot and/or League of Legends? 

Again, I have no problem with this, I'm just making sure it is clear moving forward {{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
